<br>
<br>
1.  Using FoT, then clicking a spell casting item before the bolt lands causes no spell focus.<br>
2.  Using a BWS with no following spell causes a focus to happen.<br>
3.  Using FoT with no following spell causes a focus to happen.<br>
4.  Using BoBC never focus's.<br>
<br>
Ok, the trick here is DEFINATELY something to do with the time the spell lands, and the CURRENT status of the caster.  Perhaps as suggested, if a bolt of any type lands at the same point a click item is being cast, the game will perform a check for what the legal source is.  The check will come back (an item) and the spell will not focus.  <br>
<br>
Here is a test to perform:<br>
I sold my BWS when I got my BoBC.  Can somebody with a staff click to cast with a focus bracer on, and then click again as soon as the bolt leaves your hand?  If our theories are correct, it should not focus.  Where as, if you just click to cast, then wait for it to land, it should focus. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
