Here is a test to perform:<br>
I sold my BWS when I got my BoBC. Can somebody with a staff click to cast with a focus bracer on, and then click again as soon as the bolt leaves your hand? If our theories are correct, it should not focus. Where as, if you just click to cast, then wait for it to land, it should focus. <br>
----------------------------------------------------------<br>
I have tried that.  If you follow up a Burnt Wood Staff with an another cast before the Bolt hits, it does focus and it also checks magic resistance.  I suspect it is because it is the same spell and the game knows how to apply the effects.  <br>
<br>
The thing to test is fire the Burnt Wood Staff and then follow up with another clicky/different spell with different resists before the bolt hits.  <br>
<br>
This was what I was doing when I noticed the BWS hitting for 333 against the Wasps in Burning Woods which are highly fire resistant and normally never hit for 333.  I only developed this theory of what was happening after I read this thread and have not tested.  Last night, I got involved in a Guild corpse retrieval {Which ended up including mine as well before the night was over} and did not get a chance to test it.  However, I will test it this weekend and report back.  <br>
